com.noctarius.tengi.core.serialization.debugger

Interface DebuggableProtocol

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Protocol

    public interface DebuggableProtocol
extends Protocol
    The DebuggableProtocol is a special type of Protocol that is able to identify types in a byte-stream before the actual deserialization happens.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • findType

        <T> Class<T> findType(Decoder decoder)

        Returns the real type of the next object in the stream which can be the simple type for Marshaller implementations that handle just one type or it can read additional information from the stream to gather necessary type information.

        If additional read operations are executed, the stream is automatically reset to the position before calling this method. No additional preparation is necessary.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the object following up in the stream
        Parameters:
        decoder - the Decoder to read from
        Returns:
        the type of the next object in the stream
